{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01EjeNMNdvoVeb6Em4Uu7eLr","type":"tool_result","content":"116-| Backward compatibility | Workflows without `driver` field default to `claude-code` |\n117-| gstack integration | gstack skills loaded into claude-code driver sessions via config |\n118-| omo integration | omo agents loaded into opencode driver sessions via config |\n119:| Driver capability matrix | Docs showing what each driver can/cannot do |\n120:| Cost-based routing hints | Suggest cheaper driver for simple tasks |\n121-\n122-### Post-MVP Features (Expansion)\n123-\n--\n139-| Cross-framework context passing loses information | Verification gets incomplete picture | Output contracts are explicit JSON — test with round-trip validation |\n140-| Driver spawn latency too high | UX degradation | Profile first, optimize later. 3s target is generous for CLI cold start |\n141-| Codex/OpenCode CLI auth model incompatible with headless use | Can't run in autonomous loop | Test headless auth early. Fall back to whichever driver works first |\n142:| Framework CLIs have different permission/sandbox models | Tasks fail on one driver but not another | Driver capability matrix — document what each driver can/cannot do, fail fast with clear error |\n143-\n144-**Market Risks:**\n145-\n--\n292-\n293-### Innovation Risk Mitigation\n294-\n295:See **Project Scoping & Phased Development → Risk Mitigation Strategy** for full risk analysis. Key innovation-specific risks: CLI output format instability (mitigated by pinned versions + integration tests), cross-framework context loss (mitigated by explicit output contracts), and framework permission model differences (mitigated by driver capability matrix).\n296-\n297-## Developer Tool Specific Requirements\n298-\n--\n343-\n344-### Documentation\n345-\n346:- Driver docs in `docs/drivers/` — one page per driver covering: auth setup, supported models, capability matrix, known limitations\n347-- No YAML config files for drivers — drivers are code, not user-configurable templates\n348-- Workflow YAML examples in `docs/workflows/` showing common multi-framework patterns\n349-\n--\n420-\n421-- FR34: System can accumulate cost per driver across a workflow run\n422-- FR35: System can display total cost per driver in the TUI\n423:- FR36: System can suggest a cheaper driver for tasks that don't require the capabilities of the configured driver (routing hint — advisory, not automatic)\n424-\n425-### Driver Capability Matrix\n426-\n427:- FR37: System can document each driver's capabilities (source access, browser access, MCP support, tool restrictions) in a queryable format\n428:- FR38: System can warn at workflow start if a task's requirements (e.g., source_access: false) conflict with the driver's capabilities\n429-\n430-### Out of Scope (Explicitly Excluded from MVP)\n431-"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01FEeigjd5nRWkRCota9R2KA","session_id":"cf16e575-8267-4c58-a992-20b07458710f","uuid":"743d386d-21f0-47e0-8c67-c418a2f346c5","timestamp":"2026-04-03T13:16:01.004Z"}
