{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019QrcG1igHudCLQKkvaTp2X","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Story 15.3: Driver Capability Matrix & Routing Hints\n2\t\n3\tStatus: ready-for-dev\n4\t\n5\t<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n6\t\n7\t## Story\n8\t\n9\tAs a user,\n10\tI want the system to warn me about capability conflicts at workflow start and suggest cheaper driver alternatives,\n11\tso that I avoid misconfigurations and optimize costs.\n12\t\n13\t## Acceptance Criteria\n14\t\n15\t1. **Given** a workflow where a task specifies `plugins: ['gstack']` on a `codex` driver (which has `supportsPlugins: false`)\n16\t   **When** the workflow engine runs the pre-flight check at workflow start\n17\t   **Then** a warning message is emitted listing the task name, the conflicting capability (`supportsPlugins`), and the driver name\n18\t   **And** the workflow continues executing (warning is advisory, not a hard stop)\n19\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n20\t\n21\t2. **Given** a workflow where all tasks use drivers whose capabilities satisfy the task requirements\n22\t   **When** the workflow engine runs the pre-flight check\n23\t   **Then** no capability conflict warnings are emitted\n24\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n25\t\n26\t3. **Given** the CLI command `codeharness drivers`\n27\t   **When** invoked with no arguments\n28\t   **Then** it outputs a JSON object where each key is a registered driver name and each value contains `defaultModel`, `capabilities` (the full `DriverCapabilities` object), and a human-readable `description` string\n29\t   **And** the process exits with code 0\n30\t   <!-- verification: runtime-provable -->\n31\t\n32\t4. **Given** the CLI command `codeharness drivers`\n33\t   **When** invoked with the `--json` flag\n34\t   **Then** the output is valid JSON parseable by `JSON.parse()` with the same structure as AC #3\n35\t   <!-- verification: runtime-provable -->\n36\t\n37\t5. **Given** a workflow where a task uses `claude-code` (which costs >2x a cheaper capable alternative like `codex`)\n38\t   **When** the pre-flight capability check runs at workflow start\n39\t   **Then** an advisory message is displayed: `Advisory: task \"{taskName}\" uses {driver} — {cheaperDriver} could handle this task at lower cost`\n40\t   **And** the workflow continues executing (advisory only, not a hard stop)\n41\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n42\t\n43\t6. **Given** a workflow where a task uses the cheapest capable driver\n44\t   **When** the pre-flight capability check runs\n45\t   **Then** no routing hint advisory is emitted for that task\n46\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n47\t\n48\t7. **Given** the `DriverCapabilities` interface in `types.ts`\n49\t   **When** inspected\n50\t   **Then** it includes a `costTier` field of type `number` (1 = cheapest, higher = more expensive)\n51\t   **And** each driver sets its own `costTier` value\n52\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n53\t\n54\t8. **Given** the `checkCapabilityConflicts()` function\n55\t   **When** called with a `ResolvedWorkflow`\n56\t   **Then** it returns an array of `CapabilityWarning` objects, each with `taskName`, `driverName`, `capability`, and `message` fields\n57\t   **And** the function is a pure query (no side effects, no thrown errors)\n58\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n59\t\n60\t9. **Given** the `suggestCheaperDriver()` function in `factory.ts`\n61\t   **When** called with a driver name and its task's required capabilities\n62\t   **Then** it returns the name of the cheapest registered driver whose capabilities are a superset of the required capabilities, or `null` if no cheaper alternative exists\n63\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n64\t\n65\t10. **Given** `npm run build` is executed after all changes\n66\t    **When** the build completes\n67\t    **Then** it succeeds with zero TypeScript errors\n68\t    <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n69\t\n70\t11. **Given** `npm run test:unit` is executed after all changes\n71\t    **When** the tests complete\n72\t    **Then** all existing tests pass with zero regressions\n73\t    <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n74\t\n75\t12. **Given** no new file exceeds 300 lines\n76\t    **When** line count is checked for all modified/created files\n77\t    **Then** every source file stays under 300 lines\n78\t    <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n79\t\n80\t## Tasks / Subtasks\n81\t\n82\t- [ ] Task 1 (AC: #7): Extend `DriverCapabilities` with `costTier` field\n83\t  - [ ] Add `readonly costTier: number` to `DriverCapabilities` in `src/lib/agents/types.ts`\n84\t  - [ ] Update `ClaudeCodeDriver.capabilities` to set `costTier: 3`\n85\t  - [ ] Update `CodexDriver.capabilities` to set `costTier: 1`\n86\t  - [ ] Update `OpenCodeDriver.capabilities` to set `costTier: 2`\n87\t  - [ ] Update existing tests in `src/lib/agents/__tests__/types.test.ts` for the new field\n88\t\n89\t- [ ] Task 2 (AC: #8, #9): Implement `checkCapabilityConflicts()` and `suggestCheaperDriver()`\n90\t  - [ ] Add `CapabilityWarning` interface to `src/lib/agents/types.ts`: `{ taskName: string; driverName: string; capability: string; message: string }`\n91\t  - [ ] Add `suggestCheaperDriver(driverName: string, requiredCaps: Partial<DriverCapabilities>): string | null` to `src/lib/agents/drivers/factory.ts`\n92\t  - [ ] Add `checkCapabilityConflicts(workflow: ResolvedWorkflow): CapabilityWarning[]` to `src/lib/workflow-engine.ts` (or a new `src/lib/agents/capability-check.ts` if workflow-engine.ts is near 300 lines)\n93\t  - [ ] `checkCapabilityConflicts` iterates tasks, compares task requirements (plugins implies `supportsPlugins`) against driver capabilities, and calls `suggestCheaperDriver` for cost routing\n94\t  - [ ] Export new functions from `src/lib/agents/index.ts`\n95\t\n96\t- [ ] Task 3 (AC: #1, #2, #5, #6): Integrate capability check into workflow engine pre-flight\n97\t  - [ ] Call `checkCapabilityConflicts()` during `runWorkflow()` after `checkDriverHealth()` (around line 914)\n98\t  - [ ] For each returned warning, call `warn()` from `src/lib/output.ts`\n99\t  - [ ] Do NOT throw or abort — warnings are advisory only\n100\t\n101\t- [ ] Task 4 (AC: #3, #4): Implement `codeharness drivers` CLI command\n102\t  - [ ] Create `src/commands/drivers.ts` with `registerDriversCommand(program: Command)`\n103\t  - [ ] Register all 3 drivers (import and register from driver files)\n104\t  - [ ] Call `listDrivers()` + `getDriver()` for each to build structured output\n105\t  - [ ] Support `--json` flag (default output is also JSON but pretty-printed)\n106\t  - [ ] Register in `src/index.ts`\n107\t\n108\t- [ ] Task 5 (AC: #8, #9): Write unit tests for capability check and routing\n109\t  - [ ] Test: plugin requirement on codex driver produces conflict warning\n110\t  - [ ] Test: no conflicts when capabilities match\n111\t  - [ ] Test: suggestCheaperDriver returns cheaper driver when one exists\n112\t  - [ ] Test: suggestCheaperDriver returns null when current driver is cheapest\n113\t  - [ ] Test: routing hint generated when driver costs >2x cheapest capable alternative\n114\t  - [ ] Test: no routing hint when driver is cheapest capable\n115\t\n116\t- [ ] Task 6 (AC: #3, #4): Write tests for `codeharness drivers` command\n117\t  - [ ] Test: command outputs JSON with all registered drivers\n118\t  - [ ] Test: each driver entry has `defaultModel`, `capabilities`, `description`\n119\t  - [ ] Test: `--json` flag produces parseable JSON\n120\t\n121\t- [ ] Task 7 (AC: #10): Run `npm run build` — zero TypeScript errors\n122\t- [ ] Task 8 (AC: #11): Run `npm run test:unit` — all tests pass, zero regressions\n123\t- [ ] Task 9 (AC: #12): Verify all modified/created files are under 300 lines\n124\t\n125\t## Dev Notes\n126\t\n127\t### Architecture Compliance\n128\t\n129\tThis story implements Epic 6, Story 6.3 (mapped to sprint Epic 15, Story 15-3) \"Driver Capability Matrix & Routing Hints\" from `epics-multi-framework.md`. It covers:\n130\t- **FR36:** System can suggest a cheaper driver for tasks that don't require the capabilities of the configured driver (routing hint — advisory, not automatic)\n131\t- **FR37:** System can document each driver's capabilities in a queryable format\n132\t- **FR38:** System can warn at workflow start if a task's requirements conflict with the driver's capabilities\n133\t\n134\tKey architecture decisions honored:\n135\t- **Decision 1 (AgentDriver interface):** `capabilities: DriverCapabilities` already on all drivers — extend with `costTier`\n136\t- **Gap Analysis item 1:** Architecture explicitly calls for `capabilities: DriverCapabilities` on `AgentDriver` for FR37-FR38\n137\t- **Gap Analysis item 2:** Architecture explicitly calls for `suggestCheaperDriver()` in `factory.ts` for FR36\n138\t\n139\t### What Already Exists (from previous epics)\n140\t\n141\t1. **`DriverCapabilities` interface** (`src/lib/agents/types.ts` line 27): `{ supportsPlugins: boolean; supportsStreaming: boolean; costReporting: boolean }`\n142\t2. **All 3 drivers set capabilities:**\n143\t   - `ClaudeCodeDriver`: `{ supportsPlugins: true, supportsStreaming: true, costReporting: true }`\n144\t   - `CodexDriver`: `{ supportsPlugins: false, supportsStreaming: true, costReporting: true }`\n145\t   - `OpenCodeDriver`: `{ supportsPlugins: true, supportsStreaming: true, costReporting: true }`\n146\t3. **Driver factory** (`src/lib/agents/drivers/factory.ts`): `registerDriver()`, `getDriver()`, `listDrivers()`, `resetDrivers()`\n147\t4. **`checkDriverHealth()`** in `src/lib/workflow-engine.ts` line 818 — capability conflict check should run right after this\n148\t5. **`warn()` function** in `src/lib/output.ts` — use for advisory messages\n149\t6. **CLI command registration pattern**: `registerXCommand(program: Command)` in `src/commands/*.ts`, registered in `src/index.ts`\n150\t7. **`ResolvedWorkflow`** type from `src/lib/workflow-parser.ts` — tasks have `driver?: string` and `plugins?: string[]` fields\n151\t\n152\t### What's Missing (the actual work for this story)\n153\t\n154\t1. **`costTier` on `DriverCapabilities`** — no cost ordering exists; needed for `suggestCheaperDriver()`\n155\t2. **`checkCapabilityConflicts()` function** — no pre-flight capability validation exists\n156\t3. **`suggestCheaperDriver()` function** — no routing hint logic exists\n157\t4. **`codeharness drivers` CLI command** — no way to query driver capabilities from CLI\n158\t5. **`CapabilityWarning` type** — no structured warning type exists\n159\t\n160\t### Data Flow (New)\n161\t\n162\t```\n163\trunWorkflow() startup:\n164\t  1. checkDriverHealth(workflow)          ← existing (line 914)\n165\t  2. checkCapabilityConflicts(workflow)   ← NEW\n166\t       ↓\n167\t     For each task in workflow.tasks:\n168\t       - Get driver via getDriver(task.driver)\n169\t       - Check: task.plugins.length > 0 && !driver.capabilities.supportsPlugins → warning\n170\t       - Call suggestCheaperDriver(task.driver, requiredCaps)\n171\t       - If cheaper alternative && driver.costTier > 2 * cheaper.costTier → advisory\n172\t       ↓\n173\t     Return CapabilityWarning[]\n174\t       ↓\n175\t  3. For each warning: warn(warning.message)\n176\t```\n177\t\n178\t### Capability Conflict Detection Logic\n179\t\n180\tA task \"requires\" a capability based on its configuration:\n181\t- `task.plugins && task.plugins.length > 0` → requires `supportsPlugins: true`\n182\t- Future: `task.sourceAccess === false` → could require specific capability (but not yet in schema, defer)\n183\t\n184\tThe check is intentionally simple — compare task-implied requirements against `driver.capabilities` booleans. No need for a complex capability matching engine.\n185\t\n186\t### Cost Routing Logic\n187\t\n188\t`suggestCheaperDriver(driverName, requiredCaps)`:\n189\t1. Get all registered drivers via `listDrivers()` + `getDriver()`\n190\t2. Filter to drivers whose capabilities satisfy `requiredCaps` (every required boolean is true)\n191\t3. Find the cheapest (`costTier`) among those\n192\t4. If cheapest.costTier < currentDriver.costTier, return cheapest.name; else null\n193\t\n194\tThe \"2x\" threshold from FR36: only emit advisory if `currentDriver.costTier > 2 * cheapestCapable.costTier`. With tiers 1/2/3, claude-code (3) > 2 * codex (1), so it triggers. codex (1) vs opencode (2) would not trigger.\n195\t\n196\t### CLI Command Design\n197\t\n198\t`codeharness drivers` outputs:\n199\t```json\n200\t{\n201\t  \"claude-code\": {\n202\t    \"defaultModel\": \"claude-sonnet-4-20250514\",\n203\t    \"capabilities\": {\n204\t      \"supportsPlugins\": true,\n205\t      \"supportsStreaming\": true,\n206\t      \"costReporting\": true,\n207\t      \"costTier\": 3\n208\t    },\n209\t    \"description\": \"Anthropic Claude via Agent SDK (in-process)\"\n210\t  },\n211\t  \"codex\": {\n212\t    \"defaultModel\": \"codex-mini\",\n213\t    \"capabilities\": { ... },\n214\t    \"description\": \"OpenAI Codex via CLI\"\n215\t  },\n216\t  \"opencode\": {\n217\t    \"defaultModel\": \"default\",\n218\t    \"capabilities\": { ... },\n219\t    \"description\": \"OpenCode via CLI\"\n220\t  }\n221\t}\n222\t```\n223\t\n224\tThe `description` field is a new `readonly description: string` on `AgentDriver` interface OR a lookup map in the command. Simpler approach: add `description` to each driver class. But to avoid changing the `AgentDriver` interface for a display concern, use a static map in the command file.\n225\t\n226\t**Decision: Use a static map in the drivers command.** Adding `description` to `AgentDriver` is scope creep for an informational field. The capability query (FR37) is the `capabilities` object itself.\n227\t\n228\t### What NOT to Do\n229\t\n230\t- Do NOT add automatic driver switching — FR36 is advisory only, explicitly scoped as \"routing hint\"\n231\t- Do NOT add dynamic capability discovery — capabilities are static per driver class\n232\t- Do NOT modify existing driver dispatch logic — this is pre-flight only\n233\t- Do NOT block workflow execution on capability warnings — advisory only\n234\t- Do NOT add new npm dependencies\n235\t- Do NOT modify the `AgentDriver` interface beyond what's needed (adding `costTier` to `DriverCapabilities`)\n236\t- Do NOT create docs/drivers/ pages — that's out of scope for this story (the CLI command IS the queryable format per FR37)\n237\t\n238\t### Line Budget Analysis\n239\t\n240\t| File | Current Lines | Estimated Change | Target |\n241\t|------|--------------|------------------|--------|\n242\t| `agents/types.ts` | ~155 | +10 (costTier, CapabilityWarning) | ~165 |\n243\t| `agents/drivers/factory.ts` | ~68 | +25 (suggestCheaperDriver) | ~93 |\n244\t| `agents/drivers/claude-code.ts` | ~282 | +1 (costTier) | ~283 |\n245\t| `agents/drivers/codex.ts` | ~similar | +1 (costTier) | ~similar |\n246\t| `agents/drivers/opencode.ts` | ~similar | +1 (costTier) | ~similar |\n247\t| NEW `commands/drivers.ts` | — | ~60 | ~60 |\n248\t| NEW `agents/capability-check.ts` or in `workflow-engine.ts` | — | ~50 | ~50 |\n249\t| Tests (various) | — | +80-100 | within budget |\n250\t\n251\tAll source files stay well under 300 lines.\n252\t\n253\t### Testing Guidance\n254\t\n255\t- **Vitest** (not Jest). Use `vi.fn()`, `vi.mock()`, `vi.mocked()`.\n256\t- For `suggestCheaperDriver`: test in `src/lib/agents/__tests__/factory.test.ts` — register mock drivers with different costTiers, verify cheapest capable is returned.\n257\t- For `checkCapabilityConflicts`: test with mock workflows — create `ResolvedWorkflow` objects with tasks that have plugins on capability-mismatched drivers.\n258\t- For `codeharness drivers`: follow pattern in `src/commands/__tests__/status.test.ts` or `src/commands/__tests__/stats.test.ts`.\n259\t- Use `resetDrivers()` in `beforeEach` for test isolation (already done in factory tests).\n260\t\n261\t### Previous Story Intelligence (15-2)\n262\t\n263\t- Story 15-2 added per-story cost tracking. Pattern: extend types first, then wire into system, then tests.\n264\t- 4624 tests at end of 15-2. Expect to add ~15-20 new tests.\n265\t- Build is clean. TypeScript strict mode is on.\n266\t- Key learning: keep renderer/controller changes minimal; the per-story cost bug from 15-2 code review (cost-loss on story key change) shows that state transitions need careful snapshot logic. This story doesn't touch renderer state, so no similar risk.\n267\t\n268\t### Git Intelligence\n269\t\n270\tLast commits:\n271\t- `bdca2ca feat: story 15-2-cost-tracking-per-driver — Cost Tracking Per Driver`\n272\t- `dcaf19b feat: story 15-1-plugin-pass-through-configuration — Plugin Pass-Through Configuration`\n273\t\n274\tPattern: stories in Epic 15 follow type-extension → logic → integration → CLI → tests flow.\n275\t\n276\t### References\n277\t\n278\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-multi-framework.md#Story 6.3: Driver Capability Matrix & Routing Hints]\n279\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-multi-framework.md — Decision 1, Gap Analysis items 1-2]\n280\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd.md — FR36, FR37, FR38]\n281\t- [Source: src/lib/agents/types.ts — DriverCapabilities interface, AgentDriver interface]\n282\t- [Source: src/lib/agents/drivers/factory.ts — driver registry, listDrivers(), getDriver()]\n283\t- [Source: src/lib/agents/drivers/claude-code.ts — ClaudeCodeDriver.capabilities]\n284\t- [Source: src/lib/agents/drivers/codex.ts — CodexDriver.capabilities (supportsPlugins: false)]\n285\t- [Source: src/lib/agents/drivers/opencode.ts — OpenCodeDriver.capabilities]\n286\t- [Source: src/lib/workflow-engine.ts — checkDriverHealth(), runWorkflow() line 914]\n287\t- [Source: src/lib/agents/index.ts — public API re-exports]\n288\t- [Source: src/index.ts — CLI command registration pattern]\n289\t\n290\t## Files to Change\n291\t\n292\t- `src/lib/agents/types.ts` — Add `costTier: number` to `DriverCapabilities`; add `CapabilityWarning` interface\n293\t- `src/lib/agents/drivers/claude-code.ts` — Add `costTier: 3` to capabilities\n294\t- `src/lib/agents/drivers/codex.ts` — Add `costTier: 1` to capabilities\n295\t- `src/lib/agents/drivers/opencode.ts` — Add `costTier: 2` to capabilities\n296\t- `src/lib/agents/drivers/factory.ts` — Add `suggestCheaperDriver()` function\n297\t- `src/lib/agents/capability-check.ts` — NEW: `checkCapabilityConflicts()` function\n298\t- `src/lib/agents/index.ts` — Export new functions and types\n299\t- `src/lib/workflow-engine.ts` — Call `checkCapabilityConflicts()` in `runWorkflow()` after health check\n300\t- `src/commands/drivers.ts` — NEW: `registerDriversCommand()` for `codeharness drivers` CLI\n301\t- `src/index.ts` — Register drivers command\n302\t- `src/lib/agents/__tests__/factory.test.ts` — Tests for `suggestCheaperDriver()`\n303\t- `src/lib/agents/__tests__/capability-check.test.ts` — NEW: Tests for `checkCapabilityConflicts()`\n304\t- `src/commands/__tests__/drivers.test.ts` — NEW: Tests for drivers CLI command\n305\t- `src/lib/agents/__tests__/types.test.ts` — Update for `costTier` field\n306\t\n307\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n308\t## Verification Requirements\n309\t\n310\t- [ ] Showboat proof document created (verification/15-3-driver-capability-matrix-routing-hints-proof.md)\n311\t- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence via docker exec\n312\t- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n313\t\n314\t## Documentation Requirements\n315\t\n316\t- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated\n317\t- [ ] Exec-plan created in docs/exec-plans/active/15-3-driver-capability-matrix-routing-hints.md\n318\t\n319\t## Testing Requirements\n320\t\n321\t- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n322\t- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n323\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n324\t\n325\t## Dev Agent Record\n326\t\n327\t### Agent Model Used\n328\t\n329